{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "bf534439-eca1-4dd1-bfa8-6f6aef0fed56",
    "name": "DDD-TS Starter — Accounts (Catena ERP)",
    "description": "REST collection for the DDD/TypeScript starter.\n\nTopology: Keycloak (IdP) -> APISix (verifies token) -> this app (decode-only).\n\n## Quick start\n1. Select the `ddd-ts-starter` environment.\n2. Run **Keycloak > Get user token (password grant)** — its test script saves `access_token` into the `token` variable automatically.\n3. Run **Accounts > Me > GET /me**.\n\n## Variables\n- `gatewayUrl`  : APISix base, e.g. http://127.0.0.1:9080\n- `apiPrefix`   : the APISix route prefix that REWRITES to /api/v1/accounts (default /api/admin). Your APISix proxy-rewrite must map `^{{apiPrefix}}/(.*)` -> `/api/v1/accounts/$1`.\n- `baseUrl`     : {{gatewayUrl}}{{apiPrefix}} — used by every Accounts request.\n- `directUrl`   : http://127.0.0.1:9044/api/v1/accounts — hit the app directly, bypassing APISix (LOCAL DEV ONLY; in prod the app is network-isolated).\n- `token`       : Bearer access token (auto-filled by the Keycloak requests).\n- `kc*`         : Keycloak host/realm/client settings.\n- `*Id` ids     : fill in as you create resources.\n\nSwap gateway vs. direct by setting Accounts requests' base from `{{baseUrl}}` to `{{directUrl}}` (or just edit `apiPrefix`).",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json",
    "_exporter_id": "1144866"
  },
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "Keycloak",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Get user token (password grant)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "if (json.access_token) {",
                  "  pm.collectionVariables.set('token', json.access_token);",
                  "  pm.environment.set(\"token\", json.access_token);",
                  "  console.log('Saved access_token to {{token}}');",
                  "}",
                  "pm.test('got access_token', () => pm.expect(json.access_token).to.be.a('string'));",
                  "",
                  ""
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "packages": {},
                "requests": {}
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "auth": {
              "type": "noauth"
            },
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [],
            "body": {
              "mode": "urlencoded",
              "urlencoded": [
                {
                  "key": "grant_type",
                  "value": "password"
                },
                {
                  "key": "client_id",
                  "value": "{{kcLoginClientId}}"
                },
                {
                  "key": "client_secret",
                  "value": "{{kcLoginClientSecret}}",
                  "description": "only if the login client is confidential",
                  "disabled": true
                },
                {
                  "key": "username",
                  "value": "{{kcUsername}}"
                },
                {
                  "key": "password",
                  "value": "{{kcPassword}}"
                }
              ]
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{kcBaseUrl}}/realms/{{kcRealm}}/protocol/openid-connect/token",
              "host": [
                "{{kcBaseUrl}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "realms",
                "{{kcRealm}}",
                "protocol",
                "openid-connect",
                "token"
              ]
            },
            "description": "Human user token (carries realm roles, e.g. accounts.superuser). Use the LOGIN client (accounts-web), NOT accounts-admin. The test script saves the token automatically."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Get service-account token (client_credentials)",
          "request": {
            "auth": {
              "type": "noauth"
            },
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [],
            "body": {
              "mode": "urlencoded",
              "urlencoded": [
                {
                  "key": "grant_type",
                  "value": "client_credentials"
                },
                {
                  "key": "client_id",
                  "value": "{{kcAdminClientId}}"
                },
                {
                  "key": "client_secret",
                  "value": "{{kcAdminClientSecret}}"
                }
              ]
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{kcBaseUrl}}/realms/{{kcRealm}}/protocol/openid-connect/token",
              "host": [
                "{{kcBaseUrl}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "realms",
                "{{kcRealm}}",
                "protocol",
                "openid-connect",
                "token"
              ]
            },
            "description": "The app's OWN token (accounts-admin) for calling the Keycloak Admin API. NOT used to authorize app endpoints. Mostly for debugging."
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    },
